== 2...d5 ==
Black plays the usual Caro-Kann move, 2...d5, supported by the pawn on c6. 

White may continue:

'''3. exd5''', which after 3...cxd5 4. d4 Nc6 transposes into an '''exchange variation''', normally seen in the move order [[Chess Opening Theory/1. e4/1...c6/2. d4/2...d5/3. exd5/3...cxd5/4. Nf3/4...Nc6|2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Nf3 Nc6]]. Alternatively, 4. Ne5!? is the '''Apocalypse attack'''.

[[/3. Nc3|'''3. Nc3''']], which transposes into the '''two knights attack''' otherwise seen in the move order [[Chess Opening Theory/1. e4/1...c6/2. Nc3/2...d5/3. Nf3|2. Nc3 d5 3. Nf3]]. 

[[/3. d3|'''3. d3''']] is the '''endgame offer''' line otherwise seen in the Breyer variation (1. e4 c5 2. d3). After 3...dxe4, 4. dxe4 Qxd1+ 5. Kxd1 goes into a queenless middlegame, or 4. Ng5!? goes into a sharp gambit. 

